Scope definition:


Block Scope definition: a variable defined inside a block (are known as local variables) is only accessible inside the block (inside the curly brackets '{}')
EXAMPLE
const logHouseColor = () => {
  let color = 'red'; 
  console.log(color); // Prints "red"
};

logHouseColor(); // Prints "red"
console.log(color); // throws a ReferenceError

Scope Polluition definition: too many global variables. BEST PRACTICE IS TO NOT DEFINE VARIABLES IN THE GLOBAL SCOPE.

